ğŸ”¹ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Wrapping in malware context refers to:
A. Encrypting network traffic
B. Hiding malicious code inside a legitimate program
C. Compressing files
D. Backing up data

2. Trojan Construction Kits are used to:
A. Detect malware
B. Create Trojans easily
C. Remove Trojans
D. Encrypt systems

3. Trojan makers are designed for:
A. Defensive security
B. Generating malicious programs
C. System monitoring
D. File recovery

4. A Trojan differs from a virus because it:
A. Self-replicates
B. Appears legitimate to user
C. Infects files automatically
D. Spreads via network

5. Main objective of a Trojan is to:
A. Improve performance
B. Provide unauthorized access
C. Encrypt data for safety
D. Backup files

6. Trojan countermeasures aim to:
A. Speed up execution
B. Detect and prevent infection
C. Create signatures
D. Compress malware

7. System File Verification checks:
A. User passwords
B. Integrity of system files
C. Network traffic
D. CPU usage

8. Which is a common Trojan delivery method?
A. Legitimate OS update
B. Email attachment
C. Hardware failure
D. Power outage

9. Trojan evasion techniques mainly try to:
A. Increase size
B. Avoid detection
C. Slow system
D. Trigger alerts

10. File integrity checking is mainly used to detect:
A. Network attacks
B. Unauthorized file changes
C. Password attacks
D. DoS attacks

